  "text": "In all cases, O/W emulsions were obtained. In the Fig 3 it can be observed that in the first frozen cycle, an exothermic signal appears around -24˚C which corresponds to the crystallization of water in the continuous phase; additionally is observed in -47˚C a very low crystallization signal of micro-droplets into oil phase [CITATION_1] . However, this represent low than 10%, for this reason we can consider as O/W emulsion. In Fig 4 observed de particle distribution of the same emulsion is showed. The particle size is fairly homogeneous and the mean correspond to 50 μm.",
